content.description: Slightly less chossy than the others. Gets worse at the top in terms of loose rock.
content.location: Above the large rock at the base, follows the flatter face to the left of California Roll.

content.description: Crumbly like fried rice, would need some major cleaning but could be fun if done.
content.location: 10 feet to the right of the boulder at the base of the wall. Goes up and to the right of the bush halfway up the wall.

content.description: The middle route of the sushi routes. Named California roll because it is simple and most people like it. Watch where you grab as there is a decent amount of loose rock. Would need to be cleaned to be more than one star rated.
content.location: Right of the large boulder at the base of the face, goes straight up, to the left of the shrub halfway up the wall.

content.description: Chossy, overgrown routes near the river in Lester Park. Climbs are 20-25 feet and could possibly be considered highball boulders (R-rated). Topropes can be set up on trees or conveniently placed metal guardrails near the edge of the cliff. These are just off of hiking paths. Climbs start near the edge of the river after you reach the waterfall.
